pub cached_su_info: AtomicArc<SuInfo> -> shared cache, every worker thread handling an incoming su request can access it concurrently, pointer is shared -> lock free reads of the cache pointer + safe concurrent ownership. access: Mutex<AccessInfo> -> mutable synchronised data: only the access policy state is mutable, rest is read-only. Arc<SuInfo> -> share ownership of policy object. if cached.uid == uid && cached.access.lock().is_fresh() {
    return cached;
} -> reuse cached objects if fresh to avoid db lookups.

runtime_local! {
    static REGISTRY: RwLock<Registry> = RwLock::new(Registry { ... });
} -> global variable per runtime, wrapped in rw lock ->many reads for dispaching events, few writes for registering events/hooks -> reads can run in parallel. Registry { events: HashMap<&'static str, TypeId>, handlers: HashMap<&'static str, Vec<ErasedHook>> } -> central shared state storing event metadata + registered callbacks

